premise_source_doc_sentence: , more commonly known simply as Seiko  (  -LSB- ˈseɪkoʊ -RSB-  )  , is a Japanese holding company that holds subsidiaries which manufactures and sells watches , clocks , electronic devices , semiconductors , jewelries , and optical products .
Seiko Watch Corp. , a subsidiary of Seiko Holdings Corp. , markets SEIKO watches while Seiko Instruments Inc. and Seiko Epson Corp. manufacture their movements .
Time Module  (  TMI  )  , a member of the Seiko Group , was established in 1987 with funding from Seiko Watch Company , Seiko Instruments Inc. , and Seiko Epson Corp. to manufacture watch movements .
is a Japanese corporate group consisting of three core companies Seiko Holdings Corp.  (  Seiko  )  , Seiko Instruments Inc.  (  SII  )  and Seiko Epson Corp  (  Epson  )  .
The Spring Drive is a watch movement that was developed by Seiko Epson through collaboration with Seiko Instruments and Seiko Holdings .
Seiko Instruments became a wholly owned subsidiary of Seiko Holdings on October 1 , 2009 .
